{
  "uuid": "09bcb94ad4ef720247af48d285e36c13",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Workplace Safety and Health Officer (WSH Officer)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Workplace Safety Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Spearhead the establishment and maintenance of Safety &amp; Health Management Systems (SHMS) on-site</li>\n  <li>Implement and uphold project and corporate SHMS protocols</li>\n  <li>Identify, assess, and mitigate workplace and process-related risks</li>\n  <li>Propose and enforce safe work procedures</li>\n  <li>Enhance workplace safety performance through strategic measures</li>\n  <li>Ensure adherence to Company’s Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) policies and standards</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with Statutory Requirements under MOM and NEA</li>\n  <li>Contribute actively to the corporate EHS Committee</li>\n  <li>Conduct in-house safety training sessions</li>\n  <li>Develop and execute EHS plans, trainings, meetings, and promotional activities</li>\n  <li>Conduct routine workplace inspections to identify and address hazards and risks promptly</li>\n  <li>Enforce EHS / OSH regulations at the workplace</li>\n  <li>Serve as secretary for the WSH Committee and preside in the absence of the chairman</li>\n  <li>Investigate, manage, report, and collaborate with relevant stakeholders on accidents or EHS non-compliance incidents</li>\n  <li>Undertake additional duties as assigned by superiors</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Project Budget Control</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Implement effective safety provisions to minimize re-work</li>\n  <li>Aim for ZERO accident rates</li>\n  <li>Prepare safety cost budgets for approval</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Technical Understanding</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proficient in the Workplace Safety &amp; Health Act and other regulatory requirements</li>\n  <li>Ability to provide practical safety solutions</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Other Responsibilities (Organization)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>People Development</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Disseminate safety knowledge to all safety personnel</li>\n  <li>Foster a strong safety culture across all levels</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Internal Operations</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Report any site non-conformance to the immediate supervisor</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with the project team to ensure robust Health and Safety protocols on-site</li>\n  <li>Uphold and adhere to standard policies and procedures</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree preferred</li>\n  <li>Must possess WSHO license and familiarity with safety audits</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of experience in the local Building and Construction industry</li>\n  <li>Completion of a full cycle of HDB BTO project is advantageous</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills and a positive working attitude</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply this position via Apply Now button or email to Career@kah.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p>",
